09/07/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- The wartime commander of the Bosnian Muslim forces goes on trial at The Hague on Monday (July 9th).
Rasim Delic is charged with the rape, torture and murder of Bosnian Croats and Serbs committed by troops under his control.
Prosecutors say he failed to prevent and punish acts violence committed by foreign Islamic fighters, most of them from the Middle East and North Africa.
UN prosecutors had tried, but failed, to get the trial transferred to Sarajevo last week.
(Reuters, AFP, AP - 09/07/07)
